urvived the Wreakage!</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#000000>(1/3/02 2:30:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://wsphotofews.excite.com/021/uy/9F/Fd/mf22823.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> I'm an enabler by nature. I could walk into a room of 100 people I had never met and within minutes every alcholic, abuser, addict would be glued to me...for years I tried to &quot;fix&quot; them all, to no avail and a lot of hurt on my part. I've been through counseling and have finally learned to help myself...I can also help those willing to help themselves. <br><br>As I recall there are different types of codependency...which are you dealing with...if you feel comfortable telling<br><br> <p><center> "A rescued pet may indeed rescue you..."</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/upiqa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Piqa</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/everquest/purdot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(1/3/02 3:20:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/utahdogs/msgbrd/udezboardpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> lol... I think I'm similar to you.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   A couple years ago I started reading some books, as my  life was crumbling around me, and realized I'm codependent.  I've been trying, for the last 2 years +, to change behaviors and such.  <br><br>I, too, am a magnet for alcoholics, abusers, and addicts.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It's strange how that happens... the underlying signals that aren't even perceived, and people can pick up on them so easliy!<br><br>Fortunately things are turning around now, though I still get stuck in the old patterns often. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/ukitttykat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kittty Kat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Who me?</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#000000>(1/3/02 6:49:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> I am a 5th generation addict, I simply haven't started using yet.<br>My mother is currently in the throws of prescription drug abuse and denial.  In the last two years she has been hospitalized 8 times for overdosing.<br>Last January, while in the hospital, she was mismedicated by a moron and ended up on life support for 3 weeks.<br><br>Codependency is my middle name!!<br>(Kinda how I got the idea for this board.  I need to know that I am not alone.  Meeting aren't for me, but I need moral support!!!) <p><a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/bachesandpains>The Support Lounge</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/ukingsmom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KingsMom</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.soconvenient.com/image10.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Survived the Wreakage!</span><br>  Posts: 3