guys feel at al?<br><br>One of my Aunts accused me of being an alcoholic once, to which I strongly disagreed - no not because I was going through the regular denial, but because I had already gone through the soul searching and realized what I was - a drug addict.  Alcohol was a drug that I used when I couldn't get anything else but it really wasn't my favorite.  <br>My story is weird and most users can't understand, I had a thing for coke in a big way and then one day I decided I didn't want to live that way anymore so I stopped and that was it...never craved it or anything.  But I'm not cured..I still have one vice left but I just like it so much!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I had a roommate that was a crack addict..I tried to help her but ended up turning my back on her when she used my best friend and I terribly to get drugs.  I think about her every now and then and feel really bad for turning my back on her when she needed me most..but I my own issues and had finally decided to deal with them that I couldn't be around people in my situation...am I terrible person? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/upiqa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Piqa</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/everquest/purdot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#000000>(1/4/02 1:46:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/utahdogs/msgbrd/udezboardpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> Pipegirl... I don't think you are terrible at all!  You know when I was on airplanes I never used to understand why the attendants in their little speech would say if you loose cabin pressure and you are with a child, first put the mask on yourself, then put one on your child or other person.  When I started going through recovery, I realised that the only way you can really help some one else is if you help yourself first.  If you are too weak to put the mask on your child because you ran out of air and didn't put one on you first.. then you're both lost!<br><br>I never was even attracted to men who I didn't need to 'save'.  Have had some great, responsible men pass through my life... but the 'fire' just wasn't there.  Doh!  Come to find out I have a need to be the rescuer. It's a hard thing to change!  I don't even know if I've changed it in myself, yet.  But I'm trying.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/upipegirl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pipegirl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#000000>(1/4/02 2:19:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.corinnereynolds.com/myfiles/pipegirl.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> &quot;If you are too weak to put the mask on your child because you ran out of air and didn't put one on you first.. then you're both lost!&quot;<br>Piqa, VERY WELL put!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/usoul477.showPublicProfile?language=EN>soul477</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Testing the waters...</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(2/5/02 10:15:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> New to this site, I can definately relate.  I am a recovering alcholic, with codependant behavious.  My current boyfriend, I think i mother him too much, and try to save him from the crulty of this world.  I support him finacially when he should be helping me.  How do you get out of this cycle????? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/ucynthiablue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cynthia Blue</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/everquest/purdot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silly Bean</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#000000>(2/5/02 1:47:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/utahdogs/msgbrd/udezboardpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Codependency...?</span><hr size=1> Hiya Soul,<br>I understand the cycle you are in.  It's very hard to get out of!  My BF was recently laid off.. about 4 weeks ago now. And he suffers through a lot of Social Anxiety Disorder, so it's going to be very difficult for him to get another job.  I, also, struggle with how long it's ok to be with him while he's not working...<br><br>We each have to decide our own limits, and what's ok for us.  Let us know more about your situation, and welcome to the site.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><hr width=90% color=black>"My father says almost the whole world's asleep. Everybody you know, everybody you see, everybody you talk to.  He says only a few people are awake.  And they live in a state of constant total amazement." <br>- Patricia Graynamore <i>Joe Vs. The Volcano</i><br><hr width=40% color=white><a href="http://www.utahdogs.com"><img src="http://www.xmission.com/~lucyblue/images/utahdogs/msgbrd/udsig.gif" border="0"></a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=1.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=1.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.threadControl?topicID=1.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm8.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2>